'\" t
.TH RDUP-SNAP-LINK 1 "24 Oct 2006" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_NAME@ utils"
        
.SH NAME
rdup-snap-link, create a hard linked copy of a previous backup

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rdup-snap-link
.IR KEYFILE
[
.IR OPTIONS
]

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBrdup-crypt\fR, by default,  encrypts the data it receives from \fBrdup\fR with the
key contained in \fIKEYFILE\fR. The default algorithm used is blowfish
.PP
For example,
.PP
        rdup -c list ~/Documents | rdup-crypt KEY | rdup-mirror -c -b /tmp/storage
.PP
Note the \fI-c\fR option for \fBrdup-mirror\fR.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c
This option is ignored, \fBrdup-crypt\fR always works on the files'
content. This "feature" was added because all rdup-util scripts have
such an option.
.TP
.B \-d
Decrypt the files.
.TP
.B \-h
Show a short help message.
.TP
.B \-V
Show the version.

.SH SEE ALSO
rdup-gzip(1), rdup-mirror(8) and mcrypt(1).
